
Command: api
Description: Manages the SuperSploit Command Center REST API and remote tunneling.

Usage:
  api start    - Launches the Flask API server and an automated ngrok tunnel.
  api stop     - Terminates the background API server and ngrok process.
  api status   - Displays the current status of the API server and the public ngrok URL.

Description:
  The Command Center API provides a secure gateway for external tools, such as the 
  SuperSploit OSINT Mobile app, to interact with the framework remotely. 

  When 'api start' is executed:
  1. A Flask REST API server is started on port 8443.
  2. An ngrok tunnel is initialized to provide a public HTTPS URL.
  3. A secure API Key is generated/displayed for mobile app authentication.

Remote Access:
  The public URL displayed by 'api status' can be used on any 5G/GSM or external 
  network to reach your local SuperSploit instance.

Security:
  - All requests must include the 'X-API-Key' header.
  - API Key is stored in: .data/.config/api_config.json
  - Tunneling is handled via ngrok (requires account configuration).
